  "text": "At a high level, this work addresses the noted shortcomings of existing RL algorithms [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Osband & Van Roy, 2016b) , in terms of dependency on S and H. We demonstrates that it is possible to design a simple and computationally efficient optimistic algorithm that simultaneously address both the loose scaling in S and H to obtain the first regret bounds that match the Ω( √ HSAT ) lower bounds as T becomes large.",
